          "question": "How useful are Sources B and C for an enquiry into the nature of the conflict in Vietnam? (8 marks)",
          "sourceB": `From a letter written by a US soldier in Vietnam to his family, 1967.

"We go on these 'search and destroy' missions, but there is nothing to search. The enemy simply vanishes into the jungle or tunnels. We end up burning down the huts of peasants who look at us with pure hatred. Then we walk away, and the Vietcong comes back. It feels completely pointless."`,
